   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>(-: mcandre

I mostly agree with you, but here's the thing: who knows what maddening bugs my 
bugfix introduced? So I figured it's best to wait to find out if it made things 
worse.

Turns out it didn't.

As someone who has deployed (not just pushed, *deployed*) *syntax errors*, I know 
that care is important. So I figure, this time, let's be calm and let the unit 
tests run. If the unit tests aren't all working, then now is not a good time to 
deploy any code.

After <a href="http://gitorious.org/openhatch/oh-">http://gitorious.org/openhatch/oh-</a>
mainline/commit/e07ee0dd028747fe055099c1d205ac039a787913 , the tests all pass. So 
that's a good time to know that I'm standing on solid ground when deploying code.

So: fixed! (-:</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
